00:17:20,330 --> 00:17:22,666
And they'll stop by for
the files this afternoon.

249
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:24,327
Thank you.

250
00:17:24,334 --> 00:17:27,212
One more thing, Minister.
It almost slipped my mind.

251
00:17:27,219 --> 00:17:28,248
What's that?

252
00:17:28,255 --> 00:17:32,593
I received some information regarding
Miguel Rodríguez's hideout.

253
00:17:33,802 --> 00:17:37,765
It seems he's in a building in Cali.
It's called Hacienda Buenos Aires.

254
00:17:38,974 --> 00:17:41,143
Well done, Agent. Well done.

255
00:17:42,102 --> 00:17:44,146
I'll get this information
to my men right away.

256
00:17:44,229 --> 00:17:45,481
No, that won't be necessary.

257
00:17:45,564 --> 00:17:48,567
I've already got my men there
preparing for the raid today.

258
00:17:48,650 --> 00:17:50,110
Excuse me?

259
00:17:51,111 --> 00:17:53,155
[IN ENGLISH] Well,
we can't waste any time.

260
00:17:53,238 --> 00:17:54,750
You want to catch him, don't you?

261
00:17:55,157 --> 00:17:56,450
Of course I do.

262
00:17:57,451 --> 00:17:58,869
This is the best option.

263
00:17:59,953 --> 00:18:02,456
If we do get him,
you get the credit. I promise.

264
00:18:03,874 --> 00:18:04,960
Thank you, sir.

265
00:18:08,253 --> 00:18:09,254
[DOOR OPENS]

266
00:18:10,255 --> 00:18:11,381
[DOOR CLOSES]

267
00:18:13,675 --> 00:18:15,135
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

268
00:18:15,219 --> 00:18:16,220
[FERCHO] Jorge?

269
00:18:16,845 --> 00:18:19,014
[IN SPANISH] Don Miguel
wants to see you right away.

270
00:18:19,098 --> 00:18:20,099
Coming.

271
00:18:23,185 --> 00:18:24,311
Sir.

272
00:18:25,729 --> 00:18:28,107
Just got off the phone
with our friend in Bogotá.

273
00:18:28,899 --> 00:18:31,652
Seems those DEA agents
are here for a reason.

274
00:18:33,445 --> 00:18:35,114
He says they're planning a raid.

275
00:18:37,699 --> 00:18:39,535
We can take you to Santa Rita.

276
00:18:42,663 --> 00:18:45,124
- Do it.
- Of course, sir.

277
00:18:49,253 --> 00:18:50,838
[PHONE DIALING ON SPEED DIAL]

278
00:18:54,675 --> 00:18:55,720
We got some news.

279
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:57,466
Get the cars ready.

280
00:19:00,013 --> 00:19:01,098
[CLOSES FLIP PHONE]

281
00:19:01,974 --> 00:19:03,559
[BEEPING]

282
00:19:05,519 --> 00:19:07,229
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

283
00:19:08,259 --> 00:19:09,306
Peña.

284
00:19:09,314 --> 00:19:11,935
[FEISTL IN ENGLISH] Your message
went through. Botero's the leak.

285
00:19:11,942 --> 00:19:13,110
Miguel's on the move.

286
00:19:13,193 --> 00:19:16,321
Good. Keep me posted on stage two.

287
00:19:16,405 --> 00:19:17,609
Copy that.

288
00:19:18,615 --> 00:19:19,658
[BEEPS]

289
00:19:22,286 --> 00:19:24,121
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

290
00:19:25,080 --> 00:19:26,158
[IN SPANISH] Good morning.

291
00:19:26,165 --> 00:19:27,166
Hello.

292
00:19:31,587 --> 00:19:34,006
[CHUCKLES] You seem happy.

293
00:19:37,759 --> 00:19:40,012
Defense Minister Fernando Botero...

294
00:19:40,095 --> 00:19:41,138
Mm-hmm.

295
00:19:42,389 --> 00:19:44,766
... is working with the Cali cartel.

296
00:19:46,643 --> 00:19:49,563
- What makes you so sure?
- Played a little "telephone."

297
00:19:49,646 --> 00:19:53,692
Something I said to him that only
I know was repeated in Cali.

298
00:19:53,775 --> 00:19:55,194
[SCOFFS]

299
00:19:55,903 --> 00:19:58,280
Normally, I'd say you're crazy, but...

300
00:19:59,448 --> 00:20:01,366
I'm going to show you something.

301
00:20:06,079 --> 00:20:09,458
- Those Curaçao bank files you gave me.
- Yes.

302
00:20:09,541 --> 00:20:11,877
I had a bank source help
me dig through them.

303
00:20:12,574 --> 00:20:13,580
And?

304
00:20:13,587 --> 00:20:17,090
What's interesting is who's listed
alongside Franklin Jurado's name

305
00:20:17,097 --> 00:20:18,133
on this account.

306
00:20:19,009 --> 00:20:21,720
Santiago Medina. Who's he?

307
00:20:21,803 --> 00:20:24,056
He's an art collector.

308
00:20:24,139 --> 00:20:27,643
But rumor is he does some money
laundering for upper class Colombians.

309
00:20:28,268 --> 00:20:31,271
Cleans their cash through fancy
charities, dummy corporations,

310
00:20:31,355 --> 00:20:33,607
campaign contributions.

311
00:20:34,945 --> 00:20:36,242
Guess who

312
00:20:36,249 --> 00:20:40,197
Santiago Medina worked with on
the last presidential campaign?

313
00:20:42,783 --> 00:20:44,201
Fernando Botero.

314
00:20:47,424 --> 00:20:48,459
[DAVID] There's nothing.

315
00:20:48,466 --> 00:20:51,455
Have you thought about the possibility
that Salcedo is telling the truth?

316
00:20:51,462 --> 00:20:53,037
Just because you don't like him

317
00:20:53,044 --> 00:20:54,803
doesn't mean everything
he says is bullshit.

318
00:20:54,810 --> 00:20:56,206
That's got nothing to do with it.

319
00:20:56,213 --> 00:20:59,758
There's plenty of people I don't
like but still trust. Like you.

320
00:21:07,641 --> 00:21:09,476
Darío. You see that camera?

321
00:21:12,604 --> 00:21:15,023
Maybe it caught something. Huh?

322
00:21:16,066 --> 00:21:17,144
Come on.

323
00:21:20,946 --> 00:21:22,864
I found this one from last week.

324
00:21:27,661 --> 00:21:28,662
[DAVID] Play it.

325
00:21:34,167 --> 00:21:35,252
Fast forward.

326
00:21:36,003 --> 00:21:37,212
Faster.

327
00:21:37,296 --> 00:21:38,714
[WHIRRING]

328
00:21:40,674 --> 00:21:41,736
Hit play.

329
00:21:43,176 --> 00:21:44,970
And stop... stop it there.

330
00:21:47,264 --> 00:21:50,100
See? These motherfuckers
must be the DEA, right?

331
00:21:50,183 --> 00:21:51,393
Mm-hmm.

332
00:21:51,893 --> 00:21:53,033
Keep going.

333
00:22:07,409 --> 00:22:08,952
[IN SPANISH] His transport arrived.

334
00:22:14,708 --> 00:22:16,043
We're in position.

335
00:22:17,336 --> 00:22:19,001
I'll let you know when they come out.

336
00:22:20,714 --> 00:22:22,716
[BEEPING]

337
00:22:23,967 --> 00:22:26,053
[PHONE RINGS]

338
00:22:26,136 --> 00:22:27,179
[IN ENGLISH] Where are we?

339
00:22:27,262 --> 00:22:30,113
[FEISTL] Serrano's in position.
Just waiting for Miguel to come down.

340
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:39,483
[IN SPANISH] Despite how
difficult this week has been,

341
00:22:39,566 --> 00:22:41,651
we're making it out of the storm.

342
00:22:42,069 --> 00:22:43,487
[JORGE] It would seem so, sir.

343
00:22:44,863 --> 00:22:47,532
I've been thinking about
the promise I made to you.

344
00:22:49,785 --> 00:22:53,663
Six months... until you open
your security business.

345
00:22:57,167 --> 00:22:58,376
That's right, sir.

346
00:23:01,088 --> 00:23:03,715
It's even possible that I'll
invest in your business.

347
00:23:04,549 --> 00:23:06,093
What do you think about that?

348
00:23:06,176 --> 00:23:08,220
It would be an honor
to have your support.

349
00:23:10,931 --> 00:23:12,599
Can I help you with your bag?

350
00:23:12,682 --> 00:23:14,726
No, this is almost ready.

351
00:23:15,268 --> 00:23:17,521
Take those. I'll see you downstairs.

352
00:23:18,003 --> 00:23:19,198
Of course, sir.

353
00:23:23,151 --> 00:23:24,903
- Keep going.
- [WHIRRING]

354
00:23:28,532 --> 00:23:29,696
Stop it there.

355
00:23:35,956 --> 00:23:38,375
No, that's Enrique. Keep going.

356
00:23:42,546 --> 00:23:43,839
Open it.

357
00:23:46,174 --> 00:23:48,927
[IN SPANISH] Salcedo is downstairs.
We're waiting for Miguel.

358
00:23:49,010 --> 00:23:50,011
[SERRANO] Copy that.

359
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:55,517
Stop. Go back.

360
00:23:55,892 --> 00:23:57,102
Go back.

361
00:23:57,686 --> 00:23:58,770
More.

362
00:23:59,229 --> 00:24:00,647
There.

363
00:24:04,693 --> 00:24:08,113
- Isn't that Enrique again?
- Can you get this shit to stop shaking?

364
00:24:24,754 --> 00:24:25,755
Man...

365
00:24:27,090 --> 00:24:28,758
Man, you were right.

366
00:24:29,509 --> 00:24:30,844
You were right, man.

367
00:24:31,678 --> 00:24:33,930
I'm going to kill that motherfucker.

368
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:37,787
Take this.

369
00:24:40,896 --> 00:24:42,022
Careful with this.

370
00:24:54,951 --> 00:24:56,912
[PHONE RINGING]

371
00:24:59,247 --> 00:25:01,750
[AUDIO PLAYING IN HEADPHONES]

372
00:25:03,168 --> 00:25:04,669
Fuck, he's not answering.

373
00:25:09,216 --> 00:25:10,926
[RINGING CONTINUES]

374
00:25:25,649 --> 00:25:26,733
Here.

375
00:25:28,818 --> 00:25:29,950
Thank you.

376
00:25:32,248 --> 00:25:33,316
[BEEPS]

377
00:25:33,323 --> 00:25:34,658
- Hello.
- [DAVID] Dad.

378
00:25:34,741 --> 00:25:35,951
It's him.

379
00:25:36,368 --> 00:25:38,370
It's that bastard, Salcedo.

380
00:25:38,453 --> 00:25:41,083
David, again with this bullshit?
When will you stop?

381
00:25:41,090 --> 00:25:42,158
Listen to me.

382
00:25:42,165 --> 00:25:45,252
I found the DEA hideout. The one
Enrique told us Salcedo knew about.

383
00:25:45,335 --> 00:25:47,602
And on the same street,
there's a hotel with a camera

384
00:25:47,609 --> 00:25:49,727
pointed towards the street.

385
00:25:49,798 --> 00:25:53,677
We checked the video with Darío,
and we saw the DEA, Enrique,

386
00:25:53,760 --> 00:25:56,096
and that motherfucker Salcedo, Dad.

387
00:25:58,056 --> 00:25:59,432
Are you sure about that?

388
00:25:59,516 --> 00:26:02,269
One hundred percent.
I checked the plates.

389
00:26:03,311 --> 00:26:04,729
Dad, think about it.

390
00:26:04,813 --> 00:26:06,771
He's trying to take you
out of a safe place

391
00:26:06,778 --> 00:26:08,920
so they can catch you in the open.

392
00:26:09,401 --> 00:26:10,783
It's a trap, Dad.

393
00:26:13,154 --> 00:26:14,155
Dad...

394
00:26:15,782 --> 00:26:16,950
I'll call you back.

395
00:26:28,670 --> 00:26:30,880
Jorge. Don Miguel asked me to tell you

396
00:26:30,964 --> 00:26:33,758
that he needs your help with
something before we leave.

397
00:26:37,762 --> 00:26:39,097
Jorge?

398
00:26:41,808 --> 00:26:43,308
Yes.

399
00:26:47,022 --> 00:26:49,899
[IN ENGLISH] Fuck.
They just called him back inside.

400
00:26:50,483 --> 00:26:51,901
[TIRES SCREECHING]

401
00:27:02,996 --> 00:27:04,039
Shit.

402
00:27:11,421 --> 00:27:13,715
David Rodríguez just showed
up at the Salcedos'.

403
00:27:19,637 --> 00:27:21,806
NO SERVICE

404
00:27:25,518 --> 00:27:26,519
They know.

405
00:27:26,603 --> 00:27:27,979
- [PEÑA] Are you sure?
- Has to be.

406
00:27:28,063 --> 00:27:30,231
They called him back inside.
David's at the Salcedos'...

407
00:27:30,315 --> 00:27:32,809
- Just wait, wait.
- [FEISTL] We have to go in and get him.

408
00:27:34,110 --> 00:27:36,196
We stick to the plan.
When Miguel moves, we get him.

409
00:27:36,279 --> 00:27:37,280
They're gonna kill him.

410
00:27:37,364 --> 00:27:39,240
Yeah, well, he might already be dead.

411
00:27:39,324 --> 00:27:41,659
All due respect, sir, we have to go in.

412
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:46,091
All right, go.

413
00:27:46,098 --> 00:27:47,158
[BEEPS]

414
00:27:47,165 --> 00:27:49,000
[IN SPANISH] Tell
Serrano we're going in.

415
00:27:49,084 --> 00:27:50,335
- Let's go.
- Mm-hmm.

416
00:27:50,418 --> 00:27:51,454
[SOLDIER] General!

417
00:27:51,461 --> 00:27:52,921
We have to go in now! Out!

418
00:28:04,015 --> 00:28:05,433
You need me, Don Miguel?

419
00:28:07,310 --> 00:28:08,395
Take a seat.

420
00:28:13,775 --> 00:28:15,860
All right, but we should be going.

421
00:28:18,988 --> 00:28:22,867
I think we're going to
be a little safer here.

422
00:28:27,539 --> 00:28:29,874
You fucking son of a bitch!

423
00:28:29,958 --> 00:28:32,252
What is this?
What's going on, Don Miguel?

424
00:28:33,336 --> 00:28:35,130
[COUGHING]

425
00:28:35,964 --> 00:28:37,132
[JORGE] Don Miguel!

426
00:28:37,215 --> 00:28:39,300
Look how diligent! Very...

427
00:28:39,384 --> 00:28:40,552
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

428
00:28:41,386 --> 00:28:44,264
Girls, whatever happens,
you don't leave the room, all right?

429
00:28:44,347 --> 00:28:46,766
- All right.
- Don't come out for any reason.

430
00:28:54,649 --> 00:28:56,276
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

431
00:28:56,359 --> 00:28:57,986
[COUGHING]

432
00:28:58,069 --> 00:28:59,154
Cover his mouth.

433
00:28:59,237 --> 00:29:00,321
[JORGE] Don Miguel!

434
00:29:01,076 --> 00:29:02,108
Please!

435
00:29:02,115 --> 00:29:03,658
Ah! Don Miguel!

436
00:29:11,958 --> 00:29:13,460
[JORGE GROANS]

437
00:29:14,377 --> 00:29:16,337
Go to your room.

438
00:29:16,421 --> 00:29:18,006
[JORGE GROANS]

439
00:29:20,675 --> 00:29:22,218
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

440
00:29:22,302 --> 00:29:25,638
[VAN NESS IN ENGLISH] Mrs. Salcedo!
We're DEA! Open up, please!

441
00:29:25,722 --> 00:29:27,474
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

442
00:29:27,557 --> 00:29:29,517
Mrs. Salcedo! DEA!

443
00:29:30,351 --> 00:29:31,936
- DEA?
- Yes!

444
00:29:33,438 --> 00:29:35,273
Daniel Van Ness.
There's two men out front.

445
00:29:35,356 --> 00:29:36,983
They're here for you. Stay close.

446
00:29:40,862 --> 00:29:42,680
[IN SPANISH] Let's go through the back.

447
00:29:48,328 --> 00:29:50,121
[GRUNTING]

448
00:29:55,460 --> 00:29:58,338
I believed you over my own son.

449
00:30:00,131 --> 00:30:02,258
You took my money.

450
00:30:03,176 --> 00:30:05,553
I let you protect my family.

451
00:30:07,597 --> 00:30:11,935
You listened to our private
conversations, you son of a bitch.

452
00:30:20,652 --> 00:30:22,570
I gave you all my trust.

453
00:30:22,904 --> 00:30:25,949
And what did it mean to you? Shit.

454
00:30:26,032 --> 00:30:27,033
Nothing.

455
00:30:28,535 --> 00:30:30,036
You're an animal.

456
00:30:31,496 --> 00:30:34,707
You're a little wharf rat.

457
00:30:35,041 --> 00:30:38,628
Not even that. A rat has
more dignity than you.

458
00:30:38,711 --> 00:30:40,964
Do you know what I've
just done, motherfucker?

459
00:30:41,047 --> 00:30:44,217
I told David to go to your house...

460
00:30:45,426 --> 00:30:50,348
and kill your wife and
daughters, you motherfucker!

461
00:30:51,432 --> 00:30:52,809
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

462
00:30:52,892 --> 00:30:54,227
[DAVID IN SPANISH] Mrs. Salcedo.

463
00:30:55,812 --> 00:30:56,813
[IN ENGLISH] My kids.

464
00:30:56,896 --> 00:31:00,066
Get to their room. Stay there. Go.

465
00:31:00,149 --> 00:31:02,026
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

466
00:31:02,110 --> 00:31:04,654
[DAVID IN SPANISH] Ma'am,
please open up.

467
00:31:05,196 --> 00:31:06,990
Girls, stop folding, please.

468
00:31:07,073 --> 00:31:08,783
Back here. Go back here.

469
00:31:08,867 --> 00:31:10,660
Back! Here.

470
00:31:11,786 --> 00:31:13,955
[DAVID] I want to talk, Mrs.
Salcedo. Open up.

471
00:31:24,299 --> 00:31:25,800
- [GUNSHOT]
- [GRUNTS]

472
00:31:29,679 --> 00:31:30,722
[TIRES SCREECHING]

473
00:31:34,475 --> 00:31:36,269
- [MEN SHOUTING]
- [GUNFIRE]

474
00:31:37,729 --> 00:31:39,188
[MAN] Keep shooting!

475
00:31:42,191 --> 00:31:44,527
I know you're in there, Mrs. Salcedo.

476
00:31:52,744 --> 00:31:55,455
Don Miguel! The DEA is in the building.

477
00:31:55,955 --> 00:31:57,658
[MIGUEL] Get María and
the boy into a car.

478
00:31:57,665 --> 00:31:59,250
Sir, you should come as well.

479
00:31:59,334 --> 00:32:00,959
[MIGUEL] Get the fuck out of here!

480
00:32:01,544 --> 00:32:03,004
[JORGE GRUNTS]

481
00:32:06,549 --> 00:32:07,717
[SHATTERING]

482
00:32:30,490 --> 00:32:32,533
[JORGE GRUNTING]

483
00:32:36,329 --> 00:32:39,666
Give me that shit.
Get out. Motherfucker!

484
00:32:39,749 --> 00:32:41,000
[GRUNTING]

485
00:32:47,799 --> 00:32:49,968
Fucking rat, die!

486
00:33:17,370 --> 00:33:18,371
Go!

487
00:33:29,311 --> 00:33:30,538
[PANTING]

488
00:33:41,060 --> 00:33:42,103
[SCREAMS]

489
00:33:42,186 --> 00:33:45,106
Don Miguel, we have to leave right now!

490
00:33:45,189 --> 00:33:47,859
Don Miguel! Don Miguel!

491
00:33:52,989 --> 00:33:54,198
[YELPS, THUMPS]

492
00:33:56,159 --> 00:33:58,619
- Don Miguel, we have to go!
- Kill him!

493
00:34:03,708 --> 00:34:04,786
[PANTS]

494
00:34:05,209 --> 00:34:06,878
[GROANING]

495
00:34:07,587 --> 00:34:09,756
[GASPS, COUGHS]

496
00:34:10,965 --> 00:34:11,966
[CAR ENGINE STARTS]

497
00:34:12,050 --> 00:34:14,177
[TIRES SCREECHING]

498
00:34:20,808 --> 00:34:22,310
[GROANS]

499
00:34:23,561 --> 00:34:25,229
[COUGHING]

500
00:34:25,313 --> 00:34:27,273
[IN ENGLISH] You're okay. You're okay.

501
00:34:28,191 --> 00:34:29,484
Where's Miguel?

502
00:34:29,567 --> 00:34:31,235
[PANTING]

503
00:34:31,861 --> 00:34:33,237
Where's Miguel?

504
00:34:37,283 --> 00:34:38,493
[EXHALING]

505
00:34:52,799 --> 00:34:54,566
[IN SPANISH] Go out the other door.

506
00:34:57,136 --> 00:34:58,565
[MIGUEL] Hurry up, damn it!

507
00:34:58,930 --> 00:35:00,598
[SCREECHING]

508
00:35:04,894 --> 00:35:05,895
